docs: BitNet compatibility analysis — fundamentally incompatible with ONNX GenAI pipeline

Completed comprehensive 3-agent analysis (Morpheus, Dozer, Trinity) of Microsoft BitNet b1.58
architecture compatibility with ElBruno.LocalLLMs ONNX Runtime GenAI pipeline.

Key Findings:
- BitNet uses GGUF format + bitnet.cpp (custom C++ kernels), NOT ONNX Runtime GenAI
- Ternary weights {-1, 0, +1} have no ONNX equivalent (ternary quantization unsupported)
- Custom operators required (BitLinear, SubLN, ReLU²) not available in onnxruntime-genai
- Different inference paradigm entirely vs. Gemma 4 (which uses ONNX but awaits runtime support)

Recommendation:
- Do NOT integrate BitNet into core library
- If pursued: Use Scenario C1 (separate NuGet package wrapping bitnet.cpp via P/Invoke)
- Else: Continue ONNX focus, use Qwen2.5-0.5B for edge efficiency needs

